abstract: BERLIN, Dec. 28. -- An interesting attempt has been made at the famous Benedictine monastery of Maria Laach to revive the ancient mediaeval mystery plays. The magnificent church was crowded with sightseers. The altar was screened by a thick curtain, which was drawn when the abbot and the confraternity took their seats in the choir. Thereupon a host of angels all clad in white, appeared, among them being the Archangel Michael and Lucifer.
